<p>It&#8217;s quite harrowing to read history. I have discovered an <a href="http://www.w3.org/Mobile/1998/Workshop/Minutes">artifact</a>, where <a href="http://www.wapforum.org/"><span class="caps">WAP</span> Forum</a> and others debate about how to do the Mobile Web.</p>

<p><span class="caps">WAP</span> Forum decided to create their own protocols, instead of using Internet protocols such as <span class="caps">HTTP</span> or the amazing <a href="http://www.cs.helsinki.fi/research/mowgli/">homegrown</a> <a href="http://www.w3.org/Mobile/1998/Workshop/Papers/Helsinki">Mowgli</a> approach to solve narrow and noisy problems associated with wireless networking. That&#8217;s history.</p>

<p>There are such juicy quotes:</p>

